properties.areaDesc: Northern Sangre de Cristo Mountains; Southern Sangre de Cristo Mountains; East Slopes Sangre de Cristo Mountains; Central Highlands; South Central Mountains
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 13 at 4:38PM MST until January 13 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Albuquerque NM
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected. Stronger gusts to 55 mph likely over the peaks and
along the east slopes of the Sangre De Cristo and Sacramento
Mountains.

* WHERE...Sangre De Cristo and South Central Mountains, and the
Central Highlands.

* WHEN...Until 8 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. A
few power outages are possible. Blowing snow could also cause
drops in visibility. Strong crosswinds on north to south
oriented roadways will make travel difficult, especially for
high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Motorists should exercise caution while travelling. Sudden gusts
of wind may cause you to lose control of your vehicle. Extra
attention should be given to cross winds. Secure lightweight
outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 PM MST THIS EVENING
